summary: SPOOKY SEASON IS OVER. We on the Christmas train now choo choo. Co-opted this Captain Marvel vampire request with yuletide glee....
caption:
SPOOKY SEASON IS OVER. We on the Christmas train now choo choo.

Co-opted this Captain Marvel vampire request with yuletide glee. Actually that came last minute when I realised all red and white needed was green.

It’s nice to experiment. If it works, cool, ya got something new in your arsenal. If it doesn’t, you know exactly what not to do… losing is winning.

body:
Ridiculous “Captain Marvel” predictions/theories

At some point in the movie Carol listens to the song “O-o-h Child” by the Five Stairsteps, and Ronan the Accuser overhears it and secretly kinda likes it. Which is why in Guardians of the Galaxy when Peter Quill starts singing it on Xandar, Ronan stops dead in his tracks and looks shocked/bewildered. The song reminds him of his time working with Carol in Starforce.

Nick Fury loses his eye to Korath the Pursuer, and likewise Korath’s head gets injured by Fury, requiring the cybernetic enhancements he has in GotG.

Coulson is a Skrull or Kree agent/mole, but Fury uses a Kree brainwashing/memory-wiping thing (that appears to be used on Capt. Marvel in the trailer) to make him think he’s human.

summary: Saran Penulis Komik 'Captain Marvel' pada Komikus Indonesia
title: Saran Penulis Komik 'Captain Marvel' pada Komikus Indonesia
body:
Saran Penulis Komik ‘Captain Marvel’ pada Komikus Indonesia

[ad_1]





Jakarta – Berprofesi sebagai penulis selama puluhan tahun dan sukses menerbitkan karya besar, karier Margaret Stohl melonjak tajam. Apalagi ketika ia mulai menggarap karakter superhero perempuan di Marvel Universe.

Penulis seri novel ‘The Beautiful Creatures’ tak mendapatkan beragam project novel dan komiknya dengan mudah. Bahkan ia pantang menyerah ketika di awal karier sebagai penulis.

excerpt: In the next two years, there will be three superhero movies named after female characters. Captain Marvel on March 8th, 2019, Dark Phoenix on June 7th, 2019 , and Wonder Woman 1984 on June 5th, 2020. Three completely different universes with one glaring thing in common: none of them take place in the present day. …
